WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:03.503
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>
‐Hey, get back!
‐Hands!

00:03.503 --> 00:05.005
Jackson: No! Chris!
No sign of the suspect?

00:05.005 --> 00:06.590
Harper: No, but we did
recover his weapon.

00:06.590 --> 00:08.592
Wait a minute.
There's supposed to be a gun.

00:08.592 --> 00:10.844
Officer Erin Cole never switched
her camera on during the raid.

00:10.844 --> 00:11.512
Armstrong.
No!

00:12.804 --> 00:15.140
<i>Armstrong.</i>
She said his name
before she saw him.

00:15.140 --> 00:17.100
You did good, my friend.
Very good.

00:17.100 --> 00:18.894
Do you realize what
you are accusing him of?

00:18.894 --> 00:21.188
If I'm right, he's betraying
everything we stand for.

00:21.188 --> 00:22.856
So we gather
more evidence.
It's not enough.

00:22.856 --> 00:23.941
We got to
trip him up somehow.

00:23.941 --> 00:25.192
We got to
get into his head.

00:25.192 --> 00:26.443
Tell me what you know
about Armstrong.

00:26.443 --> 00:29.196
A hidden compartment
in the laundry room wall...

00:29.196 --> 00:30.489
Armstrong: You broke into
my house to kill me

00:30.489 --> 00:31.949
because I found out
you were dirty.

00:31.949 --> 00:32.991
No one's
gonna believe that.

00:32.991 --> 00:34.368
I won't be the only one
saying it.

00:34.368 --> 00:35.994
There's another cop
on the payroll. John Nolan.

00:37.663 --> 00:39.706
Aah!
Control,
this is Officer Nolan.

00:39.706 --> 00:41.250
You don't have time
for that, John.

00:41.250 --> 00:43.418
You got to go,
or they're gonna find it.

00:43.418 --> 00:44.795
The evidence
in your house.

00:47.089 --> 00:49.091
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:49.091 --> 00:51.343
♪♪

00:54.179 --> 00:56.181
[ Breathing heavily ]

00:56.181 --> 00:58.850
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:58.850 --> 01:00.936
[ Heart beating rapidly ]

01:06.775 --> 01:08.986
[ Cellphone ringing ]

01:10.404 --> 01:11.738
[ Cellphone clicks ]

01:11.738 --> 01:13.407
Sir, it's a set‐up.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.617
Nick Armstrong's on his way
to the hospital.

01:15.617 --> 01:16.785
Says you tried to
kill him.

01:16.785 --> 01:18.495
Says you're on
the Derians' payroll.

01:18.495 --> 01:20.455
It's a lie. Nick's the one
who's the dirty cop.

01:20.455 --> 01:23.000
He murdered Erin Cole.
He's setting me up.

01:23.000 --> 01:24.459
Okay, okay.

01:24.459 --> 01:25.794
Let us inside

01:25.794 --> 01:27.087
<i>so we can take</i>
<i>a look around</i>

01:27.087 --> 01:28.964
<i>and you and I can talk.</i>

01:28.964 --> 01:30.549
Do you have a warrant?

01:30.549 --> 01:33.260
Nolan, you do not want to
play things this way.

01:33.260 --> 01:36.388
Actually, sir, this is exactly
how you want me to play things.

01:36.388 --> 01:39.558
Two cops are dead,
and a third one is a murderer.

01:39.558 --> 01:42.436
We're both gonna be
under the microscope on this.

01:42.436 --> 01:44.396
So we need to play this
exactly by the book,

01:44.396 --> 01:47.190
which is why you need a warrant,
and I need to call a lawyer.

01:49.568 --> 01:51.611
[ Sighs ]

01:52.738 --> 01:54.239
Warrant's in process.

01:54.239 --> 01:55.282
<i>Sit tight.</i>

01:55.282 --> 01:57.034
Do not make this worse
for yourself.

01:58.368 --> 02:00.287
[ Cellphone beeps ]
[ Exhales sharply ]

02:02.205 --> 02:04.291
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

02:04.291 --> 02:06.043
[ Cellphone ringing ]

02:12.049 --> 02:13.842
[ Cellphone beeps, clicks ]

02:13.842 --> 02:15.636
Hey, Nolan, what's up?
Is Angela okay?

02:15.636 --> 02:17.346
Yeah. No.
I'm not calling about her.

02:17.346 --> 02:19.097
Wesley, I‐I, uh,
I need you.

02:19.097 --> 02:20.891
I‐I need ‐‐ I need your help.
I have to hire you.

02:20.891 --> 02:23.685
Yeah, of course.
Hey, tell me what's happening.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.687
Nick Armstrong
is framing me.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.272
<i>He murdered Erin Cole.</i>

02:27.272 --> 02:28.231
<i>He planted evidence</i>
<i>in my house,</i>

02:28.231 --> 02:30.192
which is now surrounded
by cops.

02:30.192 --> 02:31.568
I told Grey he needs
a warrant to come in.

02:31.568 --> 02:33.153
You were right
to demand a warrant.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.821
My job is to keep them
from getting it.

02:34.821 --> 02:37.199
Judge Paloma is
the on‐call judge tonight.

02:37.199 --> 02:38.742
<i>He's 10 minutes</i>
<i>from my house.</i>

02:38.742 --> 02:40.369
Is the evidence
that Nick planted easily found?

02:40.369 --> 02:42.329
Yeah.
He wasn't very subtle.

02:42.329 --> 02:44.498
[ Sighs ] Alright. Look,
this is what I need you to do ‐‐

02:44.498 --> 02:46.291
[ Trash can clatters ]

02:49.461 --> 02:51.296
<i>Wesley?</i>

02:52.506 --> 02:53.382
<i>Wesley, are you there?</i>

02:55.967 --> 02:56.927
Wesley, are you there?

02:56.927 --> 02:59.513
Uh...yeah.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.348
Yeah, uh...

03:01.348 --> 03:03.266
Listen...

03:03.266 --> 03:04.768
what I need you to do
is bag the evidence.

03:04.768 --> 03:05.811
Hide it somewhere else.

03:05.811 --> 03:06.978
Somewhere it won't
easily be found.

03:06.978 --> 03:08.397
I‐I can't tamper
with the evidence.

03:08.397 --> 03:10.649
No, you won't be.
Legally, we'll argue that...

03:10.649 --> 03:12.776
with knowledge of
at least two dirty cops,

03:12.776 --> 03:14.236
<i>you had no choice</i>
<i>but to secure the evidence</i>

03:14.236 --> 03:15.612
<i>until you knew</i>
<i>it was gonna be safe.</i>

03:15.612 --> 03:17.531
Well, that might fly in court,
but I could lose my job.

03:17.531 --> 03:18.949
Forget about your job,
Nolan.

03:18.949 --> 03:19.908
I'm trying to keep you
out of prison.

03:21.451 --> 03:23.453
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:23.453 --> 03:28.041
♪♪

03:33.839 --> 03:35.215
You here for Nolan?

03:35.215 --> 03:36.758
Yeah.
He called me.

03:36.758 --> 03:38.552
This is just a signature
on a search warrant.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.303
There's nothing for you
to do here. Go home.

03:40.303 --> 03:42.139
Clearly, you've never seen me
at a probable cause hearing.

03:43.348 --> 03:45.100
Is, um...

03:45.100 --> 03:46.977
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:46.977 --> 03:48.270
...everything alright?
No.

03:48.270 --> 03:50.105
Everything is
a dumpster fire.

03:50.105 --> 03:51.106
Two cops are dead,
and I'm here

03:51.106 --> 03:53.567
to get a warrant
on a friend of mine.

03:53.567 --> 03:54.985
Is there anything else
bothering you?

03:56.278 --> 03:57.779
Oh, boy.

03:57.779 --> 04:00.699
And I was having
such a lovely dream.

04:00.699 --> 04:02.492
Okay,
let's make this quick.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.119
Raise your right hand
and repeat after me.

04:05.328 --> 04:07.122
‐Hey.
‐Coming through.

04:07.122 --> 04:10.125
[ Groans ]
You got to get Nolan.

04:10.125 --> 04:11.501
Did you arrest him?
Is he in custody?

04:11.501 --> 04:13.003
Not yet.
We shouldn't talk
about this.

04:13.003 --> 04:14.963
I know you're friends,
but Nolan's a killer.

04:14.963 --> 04:16.631
You can't trust him.
You hear me?

04:16.631 --> 04:17.674
You hear me?!
Yes, sir.
I hear you.

04:17.674 --> 04:20.051
Percy: Jackson.
Dad.

04:20.051 --> 04:22.053
How is he?
The bullet went
straight through.

04:22.053 --> 04:23.263
Doesn't seem like
it hit anything vital,

04:23.263 --> 04:24.222
but he's definitely
gonna need surgery.

04:24.222 --> 04:25.265
What did he say to you?

04:25.265 --> 04:26.641
Same thing he said
at the scene ‐‐

04:26.641 --> 04:28.143
Nolan tried to kill him

04:28.143 --> 04:29.144
after admitting
that there was damning evidence

04:29.144 --> 04:30.145
hidden at his house.

04:30.145 --> 04:32.022
I‐I'm sorry.
Like, I‐I don't believe him.

04:32.022 --> 04:33.607
I mean,
Nolan's a great cop,

04:33.607 --> 04:35.358
the best of us,

04:35.358 --> 04:36.818
but so is Armstrong.

04:36.818 --> 04:38.904
Stop. Stop.

04:38.904 --> 04:42.115
Our job is to collect facts
right now, not form opinions.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.825
Understood?
Yeah. I'm sorry.

04:43.825 --> 04:47.496
It's been a horrible few days ‐‐
Chris' death, and now this.

04:47.496 --> 04:49.289
It's easy to lose focus,

04:49.289 --> 04:51.958
but that's exactly why
it's vital that we don't.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.752
I need you to stay here

04:53.752 --> 04:56.254
and keep an eye on Armstrong
once I'm gone.

04:56.254 --> 04:58.089
Report back
on everything he says.

04:58.089 --> 05:00.258
Yes, sir.
I won't let you down.

05:00.258 --> 05:02.636
[ Sighs ] Good.

05:07.349 --> 05:09.518
Commander ‐‐
We don't have to
talk now,

05:09.518 --> 05:10.769
but when we do,

05:10.769 --> 05:12.479
you have the right
to have a union rep present.

05:12.479 --> 05:14.189
I don't need a rep.
I need protection.

05:14.189 --> 05:16.274
From who?
Harper.

05:16.274 --> 05:17.859
She's in on it, too.

05:17.859 --> 05:20.654
[ "Stay Fuego" plays ]

05:20.654 --> 05:22.656
[ Pounding on door ]

05:22.656 --> 05:24.866
♪♪

05:24.866 --> 05:26.284
[ Light switch clicks ]

05:29.037 --> 05:31.289
[ Pounding on door ]

05:31.289 --> 05:33.708
♪ They not appreciating ya ♪

05:33.708 --> 05:35.877
♪ They don't see how you glow ♪
[ Cellphone ringing ]

05:35.877 --> 05:38.171
♪ They keep on underrating ya ♪

05:38.171 --> 05:39.840
Nolan, what the hell
is going on?

05:39.840 --> 05:42.926
Harper, I've really
stepped in it.

05:42.926 --> 05:44.469
Armstrong lured me
to his place,

05:44.469 --> 05:46.137
made me think it was to confess,
but it was a set‐up.

05:46.137 --> 05:47.722
<i>He planted evidence</i>
<i>in my house.</i>

05:47.722 --> 05:50.141
Why the hell didn't you call me
before you went...

05:51.560 --> 05:53.436
Please tell me you at least
taped the conversation.

05:53.436 --> 05:55.230
Yeah,
that would have been smart.

05:55.230 --> 05:57.440
Well, that would
explain why there are
cops at my front door.

05:57.440 --> 05:59.401
Armstrong needs to frame
both of us

05:59.401 --> 06:00.777
in order for this
to work.

06:00.777 --> 06:02.487
He break into your house,
too?

06:02.487 --> 06:04.197
No. My security system
would have nuked him.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.116
I should really invest
in one of those.

06:06.116 --> 06:08.034
Yep. It's a little late
for that.

06:08.034 --> 06:10.203
I am really sorry,
Nyla.

06:10.203 --> 06:13.081
Yeah, and I am really looking
forward to yelling at you

06:13.081 --> 06:14.875
<i>when we are on</i>
<i>the other side of this.</i>

06:14.875 --> 06:16.376
I think you mean "if."

06:16.376 --> 06:18.336
[ Sighs ]

06:18.336 --> 06:19.796
Be smart, Nolan.

06:19.796 --> 06:21.339
It only gets bumpier
from here.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:21.339 --> 06:23.800
♪ You got somewhere to go ♪
Let's go.

06:23.800 --> 06:25.719
Try not to make a mess.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.971
There is a gun safe
in the hall closet.

06:27.971 --> 06:30.307
Keys are here.
Lock up when you're done.

06:30.307 --> 06:31.933
We going to
the station?

06:31.933 --> 06:33.226
No.
Internal Affairs.

06:33.226 --> 06:35.061
♪ Stay fuego, stay fuego ♪

06:35.061 --> 06:37.188
Is this right?
I'm afraid so.

06:37.188 --> 06:38.523
Your Honor,
may I see the state's

06:38.523 --> 06:40.358
probable cause affidavit?
Care to cite?

06:40.358 --> 06:42.861
1538.5 PC, In Theodor.

06:42.861 --> 06:43.820
Your Honor,
I would object

06:43.820 --> 06:46.323
under evidence code 1040
through 1042,

06:46.323 --> 06:48.408
on the grounds that it may
unnecessarily reveal

06:48.408 --> 06:51.077
information, sources,
and investigative tactics.

06:51.077 --> 06:53.413
[ Chuckles ]

06:53.413 --> 06:54.956
Well, given that
the subject of the search

06:54.956 --> 06:57.834
is a police officer familiar
with investigative tactics,

06:57.834 --> 07:00.420
evidence code section 1040
should not apply.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.714
Respectfully.
What exactly
are the charges

07:02.714 --> 07:04.674
the state is considering
against Officer Nolan?

07:04.674 --> 07:07.052
Well, for starters,
assault with a deadly weapon,

07:07.052 --> 07:08.637
attempted murder
of a peace officer,

07:08.637 --> 07:09.596
and conspiracy.

07:09.596 --> 07:12.432
Clearly an act
of self‐defense.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.684
Detective Armstrong lured
Officer Nolan to his house,

07:14.684 --> 07:15.977
pulled a weapon,
and fired.

07:15.977 --> 07:19.022
Now, Officer Nolan returned fire
in self‐defense,

07:19.022 --> 07:21.316
and no physical evidence
listed here asserts otherwise.

07:21.316 --> 07:23.902
Sadly, Your Honor,
an informant has corroborated

07:23.902 --> 07:25.362
Detective Armstrong's
account.

07:25.362 --> 07:28.615
In a sworn statement,
he identified Officer Nolan

07:28.615 --> 07:31.034
as working with
the Derian crime family.

07:31.034 --> 07:33.411
Um, but their informant
has not be certified "tested"

07:33.411 --> 07:34.621
or "reliable."

07:34.621 --> 07:36.206
And with personal jeopardy

07:36.206 --> 07:38.291
as a murder suspect
in this very case,

07:38.291 --> 07:40.377
his account can hardly
be considered credible

07:40.377 --> 07:41.795
without cross‐examination.

07:44.297 --> 07:45.382
[ Sighs ]

07:45.382 --> 07:46.675
The state makes the case

07:46.675 --> 07:49.135
corruption exists
within the division.

07:49.135 --> 07:50.804
Officer Nolan
is connected to that,

07:50.804 --> 07:53.056
and there is imminent threat
to the destruction of evidence

07:53.056 --> 07:54.891
without expedient action.

07:54.891 --> 07:57.185
[ Pen scratches ]

07:59.145 --> 08:00.772
Aren't you two married?

08:00.772 --> 08:02.065
Almost.
Soon.

08:02.065 --> 08:03.692
[ Chuckles ]
Good luck.

08:03.692 --> 08:05.443
And good night.

08:07.654 --> 08:10.115
[ Sighs ]
You did great back there.

08:10.115 --> 08:12.450
Thanks.
You didn't make it easy.

08:12.450 --> 08:13.868
Wesley...

08:15.870 --> 08:16.913
...tell Nolan
I'm rooting for him.

08:20.333 --> 08:24.003
Sergeant, Judge Paloma signed
the warrant at 0319 hours.

08:24.003 --> 08:25.630
Endorsed for night service.

08:25.630 --> 08:26.673
You're green and go.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.466
Please be careful.

08:28.466 --> 08:29.843
Nolan,
you're out of time.

08:29.843 --> 08:30.969
They're coming in.
[ Grunts ]

08:30.969 --> 08:33.012
Don't resist.
Don't say anything.

08:33.012 --> 08:34.389
I'll meet you
at the station.

08:36.599 --> 08:38.143
[ Police radio chatter ]

08:38.143 --> 08:39.936
[ Heart beating ]

08:58.038 --> 09:00.790
♪♪

09:00.790 --> 09:02.876
[ Siren chirps ]
Put your hands
behind your back.

09:02.876 --> 09:04.252
Yes, sir.

09:04.252 --> 09:06.546
[ Handcuffs clicking ]
Am I under arrest?

09:06.546 --> 09:08.465
Not yet.

09:08.465 --> 09:10.675
We got to do everything
by the book.

09:10.675 --> 09:12.135
Let's go.

09:16.598 --> 09:19.017
Please tell me that Armstrong
has got cops all over him.

09:19.017 --> 09:20.351
Yeah, I can't do that.
You know why.

09:20.351 --> 09:23.063
Come on. You cannot believe
that Nolan is dirty.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.731
We don't.
Chen.

09:24.731 --> 09:27.192
I got it from here.

09:27.192 --> 09:28.777
Head to Nolan's.
Assist in the search.

09:28.777 --> 09:30.028
Yes, sir.
Sergeant.

09:31.112 --> 09:32.363
Um...

09:34.616 --> 09:35.950
Uh...never mind.

09:38.745 --> 09:41.873
Sir ‐‐
Save it for upstairs.

09:41.873 --> 09:43.750
Nolan?
Do you understand?

09:43.750 --> 09:45.335
Nolan.

09:45.335 --> 09:46.544
What?

09:46.544 --> 09:48.046
Technically,
you're not under arrest.

09:48.046 --> 09:49.547
You're cooperating.

09:49.547 --> 09:52.342
But once you're not free to
leave beyond a brief detention,

09:52.342 --> 09:54.385
that constitutes an arrest
and starts the clock.

09:54.385 --> 09:57.055
D.A. will have 72 hours to
present their case against you.

09:57.055 --> 09:58.264
Yeah, I‐I know ‐‐
I know that.

09:59.599 --> 10:01.226
Of course.

10:01.226 --> 10:02.560
But I also know
that you're in shock,

10:02.560 --> 10:04.229
and I need you to focus.

10:04.229 --> 10:06.648
If convicted,
you're looking at 25 years,

10:06.648 --> 10:08.608
which is why you need to
let me do all the talking.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.568
One mistake,
one ill‐chosen word,

10:10.568 --> 10:11.653
and you are going
to prison.

10:11.653 --> 10:12.779
But we don't have to
play it like that.

10:12.779 --> 10:14.197
The truth is on my side.

10:14.197 --> 10:15.573
And you think
that means something?

10:15.573 --> 10:17.408
[ Scoffs ] If you were
any other defendant ‐‐

10:17.408 --> 10:19.077
[ Sighs ]
What?

10:19.077 --> 10:20.245
Never mind.
No, I want to know.

10:20.245 --> 10:22.163
If I was
any other defendant, what?

10:25.041 --> 10:27.502
You are a white man.
A cop.

10:27.502 --> 10:29.379
You have already been treated
with a level of deference

10:29.379 --> 10:30.797
my other clients
would never get.

10:30.797 --> 10:32.841
If you were Black
or Brown,

10:32.841 --> 10:34.801
the police would've created
exigent circumstances

10:34.801 --> 10:36.928
and kicked the door in,

10:36.928 --> 10:39.973
shot you if they thought
you reacted aggressively,

10:39.973 --> 10:41.266
arrested you
if you surrendered,

10:41.266 --> 10:42.767
confident that the D. A.
would bully you

10:42.767 --> 10:43.893
into a plea deal.

10:43.893 --> 10:45.562
That's not fair.
I'm not that kind of cop.

10:45.562 --> 10:47.522
Neither is Grey.
You telling me
you've never bent the rules?

10:49.732 --> 10:50.984
Not like that.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.738
Look, you have a chance
to survive this

10:55.738 --> 10:57.365
because of who you are.

10:57.365 --> 11:00.869
But only if you do
exactly what I say.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.329
Can you handle that?

11:04.956 --> 11:07.625
It's been alleged
that the Derian crime family

11:07.625 --> 11:10.587
recruited you during your tenure
as an undercover operative.

11:10.587 --> 11:13.840
In exchange for money
and concealing your identity,

11:13.840 --> 11:16.426
you provided
sensitive police intelligence

11:16.426 --> 11:19.053
which helped them
avoid prosecution.

11:19.053 --> 11:20.847
Now, is there any truth
to this?

11:20.847 --> 11:21.806
Any bit at all?

11:21.806 --> 11:23.433
Absolutely not, sir.

11:23.433 --> 11:24.726
That is Armstrong's truth.

11:24.726 --> 11:26.144
He did those things,

11:26.144 --> 11:29.439
and he is using me and Nolan
to cover his tracks.

11:29.439 --> 11:33.109
Detective Armstrong
has an unblemished record

11:33.109 --> 11:34.360
here in this Department.

11:34.360 --> 11:37.739
So I'm gonna need to see
some pretty serious evidence

11:37.739 --> 11:39.073
to substantiate that.

11:39.073 --> 11:40.491
Yes, sir.

11:40.491 --> 11:42.660
We have body cam
and dash cam video

11:42.660 --> 11:44.996
that shows Armstrong making
a series of texts

11:44.996 --> 11:46.372
at critical moments
during the hunt

11:46.372 --> 11:48.041
for Officer Rios' killer.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.584
It was Armstrong
who redirected Nolan

11:49.584 --> 11:51.502
into booking the murder weapon
into evidence

11:51.502 --> 11:55.340
so that Erin Cole could steal
the gun from Nolan's shop.

11:55.340 --> 11:58.051
Look, you can see here ‐‐
Armstrong hands her a note.

11:58.051 --> 11:58.885
Do you have that note?

12:00.011 --> 12:01.137
No, sir.

12:01.137 --> 12:02.972
Then how can you know
what was on it?

12:02.972 --> 12:04.974
I can't know for sure,
but I ‐‐

12:04.974 --> 12:07.352
Armstrong says
that you and Nolan

12:07.352 --> 12:10.897
lured him to the oil fields
under false pretenses

12:10.897 --> 12:12.941
planning to kill him
because he was onto you.

12:12.941 --> 12:13.942
That's another lie.

12:13.942 --> 12:15.526
We were trying
to identify

12:15.526 --> 12:17.153
the burner phone number
he was using

12:17.153 --> 12:20.031
in hopes of getting our hands
on his call and text records.

12:20.031 --> 12:22.492
And did you get any?
No.

12:22.492 --> 12:24.535
I mean, we did identify
the phone number,

12:24.535 --> 12:27.205
but the phone had just been
activated that morning.

12:27.205 --> 12:30.208
Which is when we decided
that Officer Nolan

12:30.208 --> 12:32.418
should go speak
with Rosalind Dyer in prison.

12:32.418 --> 12:34.295
What? Why?
We figured
she would have

12:34.295 --> 12:36.547
some sort of insight
into his criminality.

12:36.547 --> 12:39.300
She also tried to have Armstrong
murdered a few months ago,

12:39.300 --> 12:40.885
which makes it believable

12:40.885 --> 12:43.221
that Nolan went to her
to conspire with her.

12:43.221 --> 12:44.847
No. No.
That is not what happened.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.849
Look,
this is Nolan's body cam

12:46.849 --> 12:48.309
from when Armstrong
shot Erin Cole.

12:48.309 --> 12:49.686
You can clearly see

12:49.686 --> 12:52.105
that she says his name
<i>before</i> she sees him.

12:52.105 --> 12:55.191
Why didn't you come forward
with Officer Nolan's suspicions

12:55.191 --> 12:58.486
prior to taking investigative
action on your own?

12:58.486 --> 13:03.241
Why didn't you instruct your
trainee to trust the system?

13:03.241 --> 13:05.159
I can see now
that I made a mistake.

13:05.159 --> 13:07.620
But at the time,
I did not think

13:07.620 --> 13:09.747
that it was in the department's
best interest

13:09.747 --> 13:12.834
to disparage a fellow officer
without additional evidence ‐‐

13:12.834 --> 13:15.837
That is not your damn job!

13:15.837 --> 13:17.964
What does the placard say
on my desk?

13:17.964 --> 13:20.675
Commander.
Internal Affairs.

13:20.675 --> 13:24.178
This office is
the only investigative unit

13:24.178 --> 13:26.848
required by
the California Constitution.

13:26.848 --> 13:28.266
Do you know why?

13:28.266 --> 13:31.019
Because police officers
are infused

13:31.019 --> 13:32.687
with the power
of the state,

13:32.687 --> 13:36.941
the power to take a life
in pursuit of justice,

13:36.941 --> 13:40.737
power that is
all too easily abused.

13:40.737 --> 13:43.281
And yet at every turn,
cops like you

13:43.281 --> 13:46.367
look at us like the enemy ‐‐
the rat squad!

13:46.367 --> 13:50.455
How the hell do you expect me
to root out problem cops

13:50.455 --> 13:52.999
when I'm sabotaged
at every turn?!

13:55.376 --> 13:58.671
We are going to tear
your life apart, Detective.

13:58.671 --> 14:00.882
And if we find
as much as a typo

14:00.882 --> 14:03.468
in the statement
you're about to write,

14:03.468 --> 14:06.721
you won't be a cop
anymore.

14:08.389 --> 14:09.891
[ Breathes deeply ]

14:09.891 --> 14:12.643
We should be tearing Armstrong's
house apart, not Nolan's.

14:12.643 --> 14:14.437
Relax, Boot.
We're doing both.

14:14.437 --> 14:16.147
Look, we got a job to do.
We can't play favorites.

14:16.147 --> 14:18.983
There is no way that
Harper and Nolan are dirty.

14:18.983 --> 14:20.943
Three days ago, you'd
have said the same
thing about Erin Cole.

14:20.943 --> 14:21.861
Y‐‐ Sure.

14:21.861 --> 14:23.362
But I know Nolan

14:23.362 --> 14:26.032
a hell of a lot better
than I knew Erin, and so do you.

14:26.032 --> 14:28.284
He's got the strongest
moral compass of us all.

14:28.284 --> 14:31.037
Maybe. Or maybe that's only
who he is when it's easy.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.205
Look,
at the end of the day,

14:32.205 --> 14:34.957
we only think
we know other people.

14:34.957 --> 14:36.417
I learned that
the hard way.

14:40.838 --> 14:42.465
[ Straw slurping ]

14:42.465 --> 14:45.551
[ Gasps ]

14:45.551 --> 14:47.261
[ Slurping continues ]

14:47.261 --> 14:48.304
What time is it?

14:48.304 --> 14:49.639
Time for
another Fresca.

14:49.639 --> 14:50.723
What's going on?

14:50.723 --> 14:52.100
Not much, really.

14:52.100 --> 14:53.434
"General Hospital's" on
in a few.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.561
No. [ Sighs ]

14:55.561 --> 14:56.896
With Nolan.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.397
Oh, he's in custody.

14:58.397 --> 15:00.691
Getting the full cavity search
from I. A.

15:00.691 --> 15:02.485
You know,
I never trusted that guy.

15:02.485 --> 15:03.903
Nobody's that nice.

15:03.903 --> 15:05.113
They find anything
at his house?

15:05.113 --> 15:06.489
W‐‐
You're awake.

15:06.489 --> 15:07.406
You were supposed to
text me.

15:07.406 --> 15:08.783
Well,
he's filling me in.

15:08.783 --> 15:09.992
That's not really
his job.

15:11.953 --> 15:13.996
As long as we're talking,
can I ask you a question?

15:13.996 --> 15:14.997
Yeah, of course.

15:14.997 --> 15:17.375
Look,
you said that Nolan

15:17.375 --> 15:20.044
came to your house
to kill you.
Yeah.

15:20.044 --> 15:21.170
But first,
he told you about

15:21.170 --> 15:23.923
a bunch of evidence
hidden at his place?

15:23.923 --> 15:25.007
Why would he waste time
doing that?

15:25.007 --> 15:27.677
Nolan's a talker.

15:27.677 --> 15:29.595
You know him.
Yeah. I do.

15:29.595 --> 15:31.264
But he's not a boaster,

15:31.264 --> 15:32.598
and he's definitely
not stupid.

15:34.308 --> 15:36.519
You accusing me
of something, Boot?

15:38.771 --> 15:40.648
No, sir.

15:40.648 --> 15:42.233
Just trying to wrap
my brain around this.

15:44.485 --> 15:46.487
Look.

15:46.487 --> 15:47.613
I get it.

15:47.613 --> 15:49.824
I g‐‐ I get it.

15:49.824 --> 15:52.285
We all feel betrayed.

15:52.285 --> 15:53.870
It's heartbreaking
to find out

15:53.870 --> 15:55.454
that somebody
you cared about

15:55.454 --> 15:56.664
isn't who you think
they are.

15:56.664 --> 15:58.040
I mean...

15:58.040 --> 16:00.668
[ Sighs, chuckles ]

16:00.668 --> 16:03.629
I‐I‐I'm sorry.
I‐I got to close my eyes.

16:03.629 --> 16:04.964
That surgery
took it out of me.

16:04.964 --> 16:07.592
I'm just...
Sure thing.

16:07.592 --> 16:10.011
We'll be right outside.
Yeah.

16:10.011 --> 16:11.429
Smitty.

16:12.847 --> 16:14.891
[ Monitor beeping ]

16:16.017 --> 16:25.234
♪♪

16:25.234 --> 16:26.819
Tim: Find anything?
Not yet.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.362
Maybe there's nothing
to find.

16:28.362 --> 16:30.698
Yeah, or maybe Nolan was trained
to know where cops would look.

16:30.698 --> 16:32.533
Hell, he built this place up
from the studs.

16:32.533 --> 16:34.368
Probably designed a hidey‐hole
we'll never find.

16:34.368 --> 16:35.703
Did we do all this?

16:35.703 --> 16:37.914
Grey said the wall was ripped
apart before he came in.

16:37.914 --> 16:39.415
Why would Nolan do that?

16:39.415 --> 16:41.584
Don't know. Don't care.
No, think about it.

16:41.584 --> 16:43.794
Armstrong insists
that Nolan tried to kill him.

16:43.794 --> 16:45.588
But then why did Nolan leave
before the job was done?

16:45.588 --> 16:47.632
Why rush back here
and tear the walls up?

16:47.632 --> 16:49.217
I'll tell you why ‐‐

16:49.217 --> 16:51.135
it's because he's looking
for the evidence, too.

16:51.135 --> 16:52.845
Woman: Bradford.

16:54.263 --> 16:55.932
[ Sighs ]

16:55.932 --> 16:57.350
You see, now,
that's a proper hidey‐hole.

16:57.350 --> 16:59.310
For a civilian.

16:59.310 --> 17:00.478
You just got done saying

17:00.478 --> 17:02.063
Nolan would build something
we'd never find.

17:02.063 --> 17:03.397
Maybe I overestimated
the guy.

17:03.397 --> 17:04.649
Mm, no.

17:04.649 --> 17:08.694
Look, Nolan's a lot of things,
but he's not sloppy.

17:08.694 --> 17:11.822
He comes in here, desperate,
rips open the walls,

17:11.822 --> 17:13.616
ends up in the bedroom,

17:13.616 --> 17:14.951
finds the opening
behind the bed

17:14.951 --> 17:16.994
filled with whatever
Armstrong hid in there ‐‐

17:16.994 --> 17:18.454
And then what?

17:18.454 --> 17:21.332
And then...

17:21.332 --> 17:23.292
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

17:23.292 --> 17:30.258
♪♪

17:30.258 --> 17:32.260
[ Police radio chatter ]

17:32.260 --> 17:38.307
♪♪

17:38.307 --> 17:40.601
You don't think
that's random garbage, do you?

17:40.601 --> 17:42.103
No,
that's Nolan being smart.

17:42.103 --> 17:43.104
He knew we'd find
the goods,

17:43.104 --> 17:44.647
so he chucked them
down the hill.

17:44.647 --> 17:46.482
Our warrant is for Nolan's
property, not the neighbor's.

17:46.482 --> 17:48.651
So, if we open that bag
without a Steagald warrant,

17:48.651 --> 17:50.778
anything we find in there
will be inadmissible.

17:50.778 --> 17:52.405
Exactly.
So let's go get that warrant.

17:52.405 --> 17:53.906
Go for it.
But it's a waste of time.

17:56.284 --> 17:58.953
What?
Look, that is not
the evidence.

17:58.953 --> 18:00.538
Nolan wouldn't
jeopardize evidence

18:00.538 --> 18:01.747
by throwing it
down a hill,

18:01.747 --> 18:03.457
where it could be damaged
or destroyed.

18:03.457 --> 18:05.084
If I'm right
and he's innocent,

18:05.084 --> 18:06.586
then that means
the real evidence

18:06.586 --> 18:08.296
is hidden somewhere
in this house.

18:08.296 --> 18:11.299
That bag is just a fake‐out
meant to buy him some time.

18:11.299 --> 18:13.384
Time for what?
To talk his way
out of this.

18:13.384 --> 18:15.595
Just remember,
don't say a word.

18:15.595 --> 18:16.304
I'll do
all the talking.

18:20.099 --> 18:22.184
Wesley: We'll be making our own
recording of this interview,

18:22.184 --> 18:23.561
as is our right.

18:23.561 --> 18:24.687
Further,
I'm exercising our right

18:24.687 --> 18:26.105
to identify
everyone monitoring.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.607
Very well.

18:27.607 --> 18:30.151
I am Commander Percy West
of the Internal Affairs Unit.

18:30.151 --> 18:32.903
Behind me in Observation
is Sergeant Wade Grey,

18:32.903 --> 18:35.281
and Assistant District Attorney
Luca Bravant.

18:35.281 --> 18:36.407
Thank you.
First of all ‐‐

18:36.407 --> 18:38.326
Oh, no.
It doesn't work that way.

18:38.326 --> 18:42.788
Officer Nolan, per government
code 3300 and Lybarger,

18:42.788 --> 18:44.874
I am required to advise

18:44.874 --> 18:47.376
that you do <i>not</i> have
the right to remain silent.

18:47.376 --> 18:50.671
Anything you say can
and will be used against you.

18:50.671 --> 18:54.717
Refusal to fully and completely
answer all of my questions

18:54.717 --> 18:57.053
will result in
your immediate termination

18:57.053 --> 18:59.013
and referral
to the District Attorney

18:59.013 --> 19:00.431
for prosecution.

19:00.431 --> 19:02.558
Do you understand?
Yes.

19:02.558 --> 19:05.394
Having received
the Lybarger warning,

19:05.394 --> 19:07.563
do you give up your right
to remain silent,

19:07.563 --> 19:10.107
and will you honestly
and without reservation

19:10.107 --> 19:11.651
answer all
of my questions?

19:11.651 --> 19:13.611
Commander, my client has
no intention of answering ‐‐

19:13.611 --> 19:15.655
Yes. Yes.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.156
I'll answer
all of your questions.

19:17.156 --> 19:18.866
Honestly, completely,
and without reservation.

19:18.866 --> 19:20.326
No. He won't.

19:20.326 --> 19:21.118
Not another word.

19:21.118 --> 19:22.161
I have to do this.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.122
No matter
the consequences.

19:32.380 --> 19:34.382
If everything
you just said is true,

19:34.382 --> 19:35.257
then why did you flee
the scene?

19:35.257 --> 19:37.218
I object to that
characterization.

19:37.218 --> 19:38.803
Officer Nolan
left Armstrong's house

19:38.803 --> 19:40.346
because he was in fear
for his life.

19:40.346 --> 19:42.014
Is that true?
Not completely.

19:42.014 --> 19:45.309
John.
I left Armstrong's...

19:45.309 --> 19:46.894
after he told me
he had hidden

19:46.894 --> 19:48.521
incriminating evidence
at my house.

19:48.521 --> 19:50.022
Honestly, I panicked.

19:50.022 --> 19:52.775
Rosalind got into my head
at the prison.

19:52.775 --> 19:55.611
She gave me slim odds
at survival against Armstrong

19:55.611 --> 19:57.613
because he was smarter
than me

19:57.613 --> 19:59.198
and more ruthless.

19:59.198 --> 20:01.325
And she was right.

20:01.325 --> 20:03.119
I never saw
the frame coming.

20:03.119 --> 20:04.537
Where's the evidence
Armstrong planted?

20:06.956 --> 20:07.998
It's in the water heater.

20:07.998 --> 20:10.751
[ Sighs ] Yes.

20:10.751 --> 20:12.169
Told you so.
[ Sighs ]

20:15.548 --> 20:17.883
We got police files, a couple
pistols, and a bunch of cash.

20:17.883 --> 20:20.302
Alright.
CSU will process it.

20:20.302 --> 20:22.763
If there's as much
as a single DNA strand

20:22.763 --> 20:23.848
from Armstrong on it,

20:23.848 --> 20:25.349
we'll know he's involved.

20:25.349 --> 20:26.559
You up for
another assignment?

20:26.559 --> 20:27.643
Whatever you need.

20:27.643 --> 20:28.936
Drive up to Chowchilla

20:28.936 --> 20:30.396
and retrieve
the security footage

20:30.396 --> 20:34.233
of Nolan's meeting
with Rosalind Dyer yesterday.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.235
What?
Sir, I'm ‐‐
I'm not sure

20:36.235 --> 20:37.528
we're the right team
for that assignment,

20:37.528 --> 20:38.863
given Chen's history
with Rosalind Dyer.

20:38.863 --> 20:40.698
What assignment?

20:40.698 --> 20:42.158
He wants us to get
the surveillance tape

20:42.158 --> 20:44.034
from Nolan's meeting
with Rosalind yesterday.

20:44.034 --> 20:45.619
What the hell was he doing
meeting with Rosalind?

20:45.619 --> 20:46.746
Percy:
It's your call, Bradford.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.205
You're her T. O.
I trust your judgment.

20:49.832 --> 20:51.625
Tim,
it's not a problem.

20:54.503 --> 20:56.505
Okay.
Yeah, we can handle it.

20:58.424 --> 21:01.677
Sir, good intentions aside,
I know I made a mess of this.

21:01.677 --> 21:03.763
You have to let me try
and fix it.
You can't.

21:03.763 --> 21:05.723
Even if everything
you told me is true

21:05.723 --> 21:08.309
and Detective Armstrong
is guilty as sin,

21:08.309 --> 21:11.353
your actions might very well
have allowed him

21:11.353 --> 21:13.564
to muddy the waters enough
to escape punishment.

21:13.564 --> 21:14.732
Yes, sir.
I understand.

21:14.732 --> 21:15.941
And that'll be
my burden to bear.

21:15.941 --> 21:17.943
But right now, we have
bigger fish than Armstrong.

21:17.943 --> 21:21.781
Ruben Derian has been laughing
at this department for years.

21:21.781 --> 21:23.365
Because of him,
two cops are dead.

21:23.365 --> 21:26.160
He has to pay for that,
and I can make it happen.

21:26.160 --> 21:27.536
Let me wear a wire.

21:27.536 --> 21:28.746
No.
No.

21:28.746 --> 21:30.122
Look, it's not as crazy
as it sounds.

21:30.122 --> 21:31.165
Yes.
Yes, it is.

21:31.165 --> 21:32.833
O‐Okay, listen.
Just...

21:32.833 --> 21:35.377
Ruben Derian is used to
playing with loaded dice.

21:35.377 --> 21:36.545
He's always
a step ahead of us

21:36.545 --> 21:38.088
because Armstrong's
been feeding him intel,

21:38.088 --> 21:41.634
but now, for the first time,
he's flying blind.

21:41.634 --> 21:44.094
He's gonna be desperate
to know what's going on,

21:44.094 --> 21:45.888
whether the frame on me
is working,

21:45.888 --> 21:47.515
whether Armstrong
has flipped.

21:47.515 --> 21:48.933
And why would
he listen to you?

21:48.933 --> 21:50.851
I'm the only guy
more desperate than he is.

21:50.851 --> 21:52.686
Look, Armstrong is burned
in this department

21:52.686 --> 21:53.896
no matter what.

21:53.896 --> 21:56.440
But if Ruben can get Serj
to admit to the frame,

21:56.440 --> 21:57.942
I'm redeemed.

21:57.942 --> 21:59.527
I can stay on the job.

21:59.527 --> 22:01.195
Ruben will see
the value in that.

22:01.195 --> 22:03.405
He'll have a new mole
with another 20 years
left on the job.

22:04.740 --> 22:06.116
15 maybe.

22:06.116 --> 22:08.035
We're done,
Officer Nolan.

22:08.035 --> 22:09.495
[ Door opens ]

22:09.495 --> 22:11.497
[ Door closes ]
He just saved
your life.

22:11.497 --> 22:13.707
The odds of Ruben buying
your act are slim to none.

22:13.707 --> 22:15.459
Well, he wouldn't
have to buy it.

22:15.459 --> 22:18.921
A meeting alone would
constitute cons‐‐ conspiracy.

22:18.921 --> 22:21.674
And if he shoots you
on sight?

22:21.674 --> 22:24.468
Then the D. A. could indict him
for capital murder.

22:24.468 --> 22:27.638
Sir...

22:27.638 --> 22:31.141
Sergeant, I know I can't undo
the mistakes I've made,

22:31.141 --> 22:34.520
but I can help
make things right.

22:34.520 --> 22:36.397
No matter
what it costs me.

22:36.397 --> 22:41.652
♪♪

22:41.652 --> 22:43.445
[ Door opens ]

22:43.445 --> 22:46.240
You are,
without a doubt,

22:46.240 --> 22:47.825
the biggest pain in my ass
I've suffered

22:47.825 --> 22:49.493
in 25 years on the job.

22:49.493 --> 22:51.453
Is that a yes?

22:51.453 --> 22:54.164
Vice has a C.I.
in the Derian organization.

22:54.164 --> 22:56.292
He works at
one of their karaoke bars.

22:56.292 --> 22:58.335
We can use him
to spin Ruben,

22:58.335 --> 23:00.880
giving you a fighting chance
to convince the Derians

23:00.880 --> 23:02.131
that you're desperate
to make a deal.

23:04.925 --> 23:05.968
I quit.

23:08.721 --> 23:11.599
[ Sighs ]

23:11.599 --> 23:14.894
[ Groans, retches ]

23:14.894 --> 23:16.854
Hey.

23:16.854 --> 23:18.480
[ Clears throat ]
How's it going?

23:18.480 --> 23:21.483
Uh, my client
just staged a mutiny.

23:21.483 --> 23:22.526
Now he's trying
to get himself killed.

23:22.526 --> 23:24.194
Can we talk?
I can't.

23:24.194 --> 23:25.696
I'm retracing Armstrong's
movements for I. A. ‐‐

23:25.696 --> 23:27.114
Wesley.

23:30.034 --> 23:31.702
You know I peed on that,
right?

23:31.702 --> 23:33.162
Angela.
I'm just saying,

23:33.162 --> 23:34.204
you might want to
wash your hands.

23:34.204 --> 23:35.748
Angela.

23:35.748 --> 23:36.749
Why didn't you tell me?

23:36.749 --> 23:37.583
Why do you think?

23:39.418 --> 23:40.794
I mean, you don't
want to have a kid?

23:40.794 --> 23:42.963
[ Sighs ] This isn't how
it was supposed to go.

23:44.506 --> 23:47.051
I wanted
the storybook wedding

23:47.051 --> 23:50.095
and the honeymoon
that we'd never forget.

23:50.095 --> 23:52.640
I wanted the romance
before the responsibility.

23:53.724 --> 23:55.476
I wanted to be ready.

23:55.476 --> 23:57.436
We can still have
all of that.

23:57.436 --> 23:59.063
No, we can't.
It won't be the same.

23:59.063 --> 24:00.314
No.

24:01.899 --> 24:03.233
Not all of it.

24:06.403 --> 24:08.614
But here's what
will be the same ‐‐

24:08.614 --> 24:11.200
You are gonna look beautiful
in your dress.

24:11.200 --> 24:13.869
And I will cry when I see you
walking down the aisle,

24:13.869 --> 24:15.621
and you'll make fun of me for it
for the rest of our lives.

24:15.621 --> 24:16.664
No, I won't.

24:17.414 --> 24:18.791
Yeah, I will.

24:21.001 --> 24:23.587
This is our path,
Angela.

24:23.587 --> 24:25.673
And it is not the one that
we thought we were on yesterday,

24:25.673 --> 24:27.466
but we are still on it
together.

24:27.466 --> 24:31.095
I promise when we look back
at this moment,

24:31.095 --> 24:34.390
it will feel like
the gift that it is.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.475
You say that now,
but once the hormones kick in,

24:36.475 --> 24:37.393
you're in
for a rough ride.

24:37.393 --> 24:38.435
Bring it on.

24:40.104 --> 24:41.647
This is the part
where you kiss me.

24:41.647 --> 24:43.565
I would, but I'm feeling
super pukey right now.

24:43.565 --> 24:45.567
So...rain check?

24:45.567 --> 24:46.902
[ Sighs ]

24:49.488 --> 24:51.323
[ Retching ]

24:55.619 --> 24:57.746
What kind of a prison
doesn't have audio

24:57.746 --> 24:58.539
on their surveillance
cameras?

24:58.539 --> 24:59.623
Sound costs money.

24:59.623 --> 25:00.958
Head back to the shop

25:00.958 --> 25:02.042
while I go get a statement
from Rosalind.

25:02.042 --> 25:03.711
What? No way.

25:03.711 --> 25:04.962
It's for your own good.

25:04.962 --> 25:06.088
You have
a personal connection.

25:06.088 --> 25:07.464
So do you.
It's not the same.

25:07.464 --> 25:09.049
If I can't handle
talking to Rosalind

25:09.049 --> 25:11.385
while she's in a cage,
I shouldn't be a cop.

25:11.385 --> 25:13.887
[ Sighs ]

25:13.887 --> 25:15.764
[ Door buzzes ]

25:15.764 --> 25:16.890
Tim: We have a few questions
to ask you.

25:16.890 --> 25:18.350
Shouldn't take long.

25:18.350 --> 25:20.436
Mm. This is about John,
isn't it?

25:20.436 --> 25:22.730
We know you talked to him
about Armstrong yesterday.

25:22.730 --> 25:24.398
Can you describe the content
of that conversation?

25:25.691 --> 25:29.194
You know,
I am so impressed with you.

25:29.194 --> 25:31.113
The way you handled
what was obviously

25:31.113 --> 25:33.991
a very traumatic
experience ‐‐

25:33.991 --> 25:35.492
it's inspiring.

25:35.492 --> 25:36.952
Thanks.

25:36.952 --> 25:38.620
That means a lot
coming from you.

25:38.620 --> 25:40.539
Rrow.

25:40.539 --> 25:41.832
So defiant.

25:41.832 --> 25:43.375
Alright,
let's stick to Nolan.

25:43.375 --> 25:46.378
Just like you were when the lid
came down on that barrel.

25:46.378 --> 25:49.089
You know, it must have
driven Caleb crazy ‐‐

25:49.089 --> 25:50.382
denying him the fear

25:50.382 --> 25:52.718
he so desperately
wanted to see in you.

25:52.718 --> 25:54.595
How ‐‐

25:54.595 --> 25:57.014
Do I know that?

25:57.014 --> 25:59.058
[ Chuckles softly ]

26:00.559 --> 26:03.228
You think the camera
in the barrel was for Caleb?

26:03.228 --> 26:04.938
Don't listen to her, Chen.
She's just playing mind games.

26:04.938 --> 26:07.524
Oh, I am totally
playing mind games.

26:07.524 --> 26:09.985
But I'm not lying.

26:09.985 --> 26:15.699
♪ Stars shining bright
above you ♪

26:15.699 --> 26:20.454
♪ Night breezes seem
to whisper "I love you" ♪
♪ <i>Night breezes seem</i>
<i>to whisper "I love you"</i> ♪

26:20.454 --> 26:23.707
♪ Birds singing
in the sycamore tree ♪

26:23.707 --> 26:25.250
Knock it off.

26:25.250 --> 26:26.919
Ah.

26:26.919 --> 26:28.754
The fierce protector.

26:28.754 --> 26:30.506
We're done here.
Let's go.

26:30.506 --> 26:31.507
We'll have I. A.
follow up.

26:31.507 --> 26:33.217
[ Door buzzes ]

26:33.217 --> 26:34.718
Armstrong's lasted
this long

26:34.718 --> 26:38.222
because his contingency plans
have contingencies.

26:38.222 --> 26:40.933
Whatever you've already found,
there's more.

26:41.934 --> 26:43.143
What did she mean
by that?

26:43.143 --> 26:44.645
Armstrong's
prepared to run.

26:44.645 --> 26:47.439
He's got a go‐bag
hidden somewhere.

26:47.439 --> 26:49.858
Lopez, I got something
for you to chase down.

26:49.858 --> 26:51.527
Sgt. Grey:
So, we have to assume

26:51.527 --> 26:53.320
the Derians are watching
the station,

26:53.320 --> 26:55.614
so you'll be on your own
the second you leave.

26:55.614 --> 26:57.950
I heard a whisper
y'all were up to something.

26:57.950 --> 26:59.368
I want in.
Forget it.

26:59.368 --> 27:01.078
You are still under
active investigation.

27:01.078 --> 27:02.996
And before you say
"So's Nolan,"

27:02.996 --> 27:04.498
there's no operation
without him,

27:04.498 --> 27:06.166
which is the <i>only</i> reason
why he's involved.

27:06.166 --> 27:07.459
Understood?

27:07.459 --> 27:08.460
Yes, sir.

27:08.460 --> 27:09.586
Good.
Then take a walk.

27:11.296 --> 27:13.882
We will monitor you
through audio bugs and GPS ‐‐

27:13.882 --> 27:16.468
You have to believe the lie
or else you can't sell it.

27:16.468 --> 27:18.345
Ruben needs to feel like
you are desperate enough

27:18.345 --> 27:20.389
to betray everything
you care about.

27:20.389 --> 27:21.807
That shouldn't be
too hard to sell.

27:21.807 --> 27:23.308
Anything else?
Be careful.

27:24.560 --> 27:26.603
But not too careful.

27:26.603 --> 27:28.146
Undercover
is all about offense,

27:28.146 --> 27:29.523
even when
you are playing defense.

27:29.523 --> 27:32.234
Are you done?
Yes.

27:32.234 --> 27:34.486
No, no.

27:34.486 --> 27:37.114
Don't be afraid to pull
the rip cord, okay?

27:37.114 --> 27:39.908
Arresting Ruben Derian
is not worth your life.

27:39.908 --> 27:42.494
<i>Now</i> I'm done.

27:42.494 --> 27:44.288
[ Door buzzes ]
Are you ready
to do this?

27:44.288 --> 27:45.998
Yes, sir.

27:45.998 --> 27:47.624
Woman:
<i>We have some breaking news</i>

27:47.624 --> 27:50.127
<i>in the recent scandal</i>
<i>rocking the LAPD.</i>

27:50.127 --> 27:53.005
<i>A source inside the department</i>
<i>tells KZYO</i>

27:53.005 --> 27:54.548
<i>that Officer John Nolan,</i>

27:54.548 --> 27:56.466
<i>a rookie</i>
<i>in the Mid‐Wilshire Division...</i>
Check, check.

27:56.466 --> 27:58.427
<i>...has been suspended</i>
<i>without pay,</i>

27:58.427 --> 27:59.928
<i>and it appears</i>
<i>that criminal charges</i>

27:59.928 --> 28:02.139
<i>will be filed at any moment.</i>

28:02.139 --> 28:04.808
♪ And now we're thrivin',
ain't nobody denyin' ♪

28:04.808 --> 28:06.768
♪ This is my squad ♪

28:13.025 --> 28:15.736
[ Cellphone clicks, dials ]

28:15.736 --> 28:19.281
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

28:19.281 --> 28:21.033
Ruben: <i>Who is this?</i>
It's John Nolan.

28:21.033 --> 28:22.659
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>
Wait.

28:22.659 --> 28:24.202
[ Heart beating rapidly ]

28:24.202 --> 28:25.746
If you don't help me,
I'm a dead man.

28:25.746 --> 28:27.372
I'll do anything.

28:30.167 --> 28:32.002
<i>Keep your phone on.</i>

28:32.002 --> 28:32.961
[ Earpiece beeps ]
We're in business.

28:32.961 --> 28:35.464
8500 team,
subject's in play.

28:35.464 --> 28:39.343
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]

28:39.343 --> 28:40.469
Lopez, what's up?

28:40.469 --> 28:42.596
Just cementing
Armstrong's timeline.

28:42.596 --> 28:44.431
The good news is that
his cellphone GPS

28:44.431 --> 28:46.850
puts him at Nolan's house
for over an hour yesterday.

28:46.850 --> 28:48.060
That's about how long
it would take

28:48.060 --> 28:50.145
to cut a hole in the wall
and plant evidence.

28:50.145 --> 28:51.688
Yes, sir.
<i>Good job.</i>

28:51.688 --> 28:53.649
Where you at now?
Cemetery.

28:53.649 --> 28:56.485
Armstrong spent 31 minutes here
after he left Nolan's.

28:56.485 --> 28:57.986
Probably saying goodbye
to his wife

28:57.986 --> 28:59.696
just in case
things went sideways.

28:59.696 --> 29:01.865
That's what I thought,
but then Tim called.

29:01.865 --> 29:04.284
Word is that Armstrong has
a go‐bag hidden somewhere.

29:04.284 --> 29:05.494
Wait a minute.
You don't think ‐‐

29:05.494 --> 29:08.038
That he buried the bag
on top of his wife's coffin?

29:08.038 --> 29:09.915
No. But I'm gonna do
some digging anyway.

29:09.915 --> 29:11.166
[ Chuckles ]

29:11.166 --> 29:12.834
[ Grunting ]

29:18.090 --> 29:19.883
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:22.386 --> 29:23.637
Found it.

29:27.516 --> 29:28.850
[ Sighs ]

29:28.850 --> 29:31.520
[ Retches, coughing ]

29:32.729 --> 29:35.023
What the hell was that?

29:35.023 --> 29:36.984
Nothing. [ Sighs ]

29:40.612 --> 29:43.281
It's been three hours.
How long before we give up?

29:43.281 --> 29:44.992
Patience is a virtue,
Officer Nolan.

29:44.992 --> 29:46.410
Yes, sir.

29:48.161 --> 29:50.414
[ Cellphone rings ]

29:50.414 --> 29:51.999
Here we go.

29:51.999 --> 29:53.583
[ Cellphone beeps ]
This is Nolan.

29:53.583 --> 29:56.086
[ Distorted ] <i>Hudson Avenue</i>
<i>and Twelfth Street, 10 minutes.</i>

29:56.086 --> 29:58.046
<i>A second late</i>
<i>and we're gone.</i>

29:58.046 --> 29:59.381
[ Engine starts ]
We're green and go.

29:59.381 --> 30:02.676
I repeat,
we are green and go.

30:02.676 --> 30:05.554
♪ Then get it all ♪

30:05.554 --> 30:08.056
♪ You want it all? ♪

30:08.056 --> 30:11.226
♪ Fight for it ♪

30:11.226 --> 30:12.644
I just landed.

30:12.644 --> 30:14.646
20 seconds to spare.
No one in sight.

30:14.646 --> 30:17.315
We're in place.
We're watching on the drone.

30:17.315 --> 30:19.609
Get ready, Nolan.
Black SUV coming your way.

30:19.609 --> 30:21.945
I see it.

30:21.945 --> 30:23.321
[ Earpiece beeps ]
Going dark.

30:23.321 --> 30:25.115
♪ I'm out of pennies
for that wishing well ♪

30:25.115 --> 30:27.075
♪ So I'm throwing bodies,
and they wish me well ♪

30:27.075 --> 30:28.618
♪ Ride the wave ♪
Strip.

30:28.618 --> 30:29.911
What?

30:29.911 --> 30:31.621
Clothes off. Shoes, too.
Let's go.

30:31.621 --> 30:34.291
♪ Caged animals in a cube,
chasing that salary ♪

30:34.291 --> 30:36.460
♪ Into this business like
a knick to your femoral, bam ♪

30:36.460 --> 30:39.212
[ Sighs ] They're stripping him
of all the bugs.

30:39.212 --> 30:40.881
♪ Wanna cross my path,
you gotta pay ♪

30:40.881 --> 30:42.215
♪ Pull on up to the ‐‐ ♪

30:42.215 --> 30:43.675
♪ Moved from your stomach
up into your veins ♪

30:43.675 --> 30:46.553
Seriously?
You wanna roll
in your underwear?

30:46.553 --> 30:48.972
Man: <i>Should we pull the plug,</i>
<i>sir?</i>

30:48.972 --> 30:50.223
Negative.
Hold position.

30:50.223 --> 30:51.641
♪ Others already
on their journey ♪

30:51.641 --> 30:52.809
♪ Fight for it ♪

30:52.809 --> 30:55.187
♪ You want it all? ♪

30:55.187 --> 30:56.104
For your head.

30:56.104 --> 30:58.148
No way.
No hood, no go.

30:58.148 --> 31:00.650
♪ You want it all? ♪

31:00.650 --> 31:02.027
♪ Fight for it ♪

31:02.027 --> 31:03.653
Don't suppose you washed this
after the last guy.

31:03.653 --> 31:04.821
Get in the car.

31:04.821 --> 31:06.490
♪ Then get it all ♪

31:06.490 --> 31:08.366
Sgt. Grey:
<i>All units, hold position.</i>

31:08.366 --> 31:09.493
<i>They'll be watching</i>
<i>for movement.</i>

31:09.493 --> 31:11.453
Drone operator,
do not lose him.

31:11.453 --> 31:13.622
Man: <i>Roger that.</i>
[ Door buzzes ]

31:13.622 --> 31:15.040
♪ Conquer ♪

31:22.297 --> 31:24.382
[ Cellphone beeps ]

31:24.382 --> 31:27.052
[ Breathes deeply ]
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

31:29.971 --> 31:31.765
I have a call for you
at the nurse's station ‐‐

31:31.765 --> 31:33.183
Sergeant Grey?

31:33.183 --> 31:34.976
Boss is calling.

31:34.976 --> 31:37.771
Probably to sing
my praises.

31:37.771 --> 31:39.523
[ Telephone ringing ]

31:39.523 --> 31:48.532
♪♪

31:48.532 --> 31:49.950
Hello?

31:49.950 --> 31:51.201
Hello, Nicholas.

31:57.833 --> 31:59.042
How's the gunshot wound?

31:59.042 --> 32:00.085
I'll survive.

32:00.085 --> 32:02.087
[ Chuckles ]

32:02.087 --> 32:04.214
I'm not so sure
about that.

32:04.214 --> 32:06.591
You have made
quite a mess.

32:06.591 --> 32:07.801
<i>You can't really believe</i>

32:07.801 --> 32:09.678
that your slapdash
frame job of Nolan

32:09.678 --> 32:11.138
is going to hold up.

32:11.138 --> 32:13.765
Still got a couple cards
up my sleeve.
<i>Not anymore.</i>

32:13.765 --> 32:16.810
You see, I've been turning
those cards over for you.

32:16.810 --> 32:20.063
<i>Who do you think told John</i>
<i>about your little hidey‐hole?</i>

32:20.063 --> 32:22.315
And now I've told them
about your go‐bag.

32:22.315 --> 32:25.485
You're out of moves, Nick.
Enjoy prison.

32:25.485 --> 32:27.654
Wha‐‐

32:27.654 --> 32:29.281
[ Grunts ]

32:29.281 --> 32:31.283
[ Inhales sharply ]

32:31.283 --> 32:33.785
[ The Bobby Lees'
"Guttermilk" plays ]

32:33.785 --> 32:35.245
Man: <i>Heads up.</i>
<i>Losing visual.</i>

32:35.245 --> 32:36.454
<i>They're going in a tunnel.</i>

32:36.454 --> 32:38.039
<i>Moving to the other side</i>
<i>to intercept.</i>

32:38.039 --> 32:40.083
Let's tighten up.
We need eyes on ASAP.

32:41.668 --> 32:43.461
You sure he said Grey?

32:43.461 --> 32:45.547
Positive.
Smitty.
What are you ‐‐

32:45.547 --> 32:48.967
♪ I left that girl dyin'
somewhere down on the way ♪

32:48.967 --> 32:53.305
♪ Stuck on that dead bus
and then left in a desert way ♪

32:53.305 --> 32:54.389
♪ I haven't slept for my ♪

32:54.389 --> 32:56.224
<i>Target reacquired.</i>

32:56.224 --> 32:58.810
Jackson:
<i>Sergeant, Armstrong slipped</i>
<i>his detail at the hospital.</i>

32:58.810 --> 33:01.563
<i>He's gone.</i>
All units,
we need to get Nolan out now.

33:01.563 --> 33:02.689
♪ After what I saw ♪

33:02.689 --> 33:04.900
[ Tires screeching ]

33:04.900 --> 33:07.235
♪ I'm just like guttermilk,
yeah ♪

33:07.235 --> 33:08.987
[ Sirens wail ]

33:10.322 --> 33:12.490
Show me your hands!
Show me your hands!

33:12.490 --> 33:14.367
Roll down your window!
Get your window down.

33:14.367 --> 33:16.328
♪ Somewhere down ‐‐
guttermilk ♪

33:16.328 --> 33:18.830
Nolan.

33:18.830 --> 33:20.123
Nolan's out of the pocket.

33:20.123 --> 33:21.124
They must have switched him out
in the tunnel.

33:21.124 --> 33:23.084
[ Smacks table ]

33:23.084 --> 33:28.256
♪♪

33:28.256 --> 33:33.386
♪♪

33:33.386 --> 33:35.388
[ Tires screech ]

33:35.388 --> 33:42.729
♪♪

33:42.729 --> 33:44.773
[ Car door closes ]

33:44.773 --> 33:50.195
♪♪

33:50.195 --> 33:52.280
You wanted to talk?
So talk.

33:52.280 --> 33:54.407
But maybe first,
explain to me

33:54.407 --> 33:55.659
the surveillance team
that was following you.

33:55.659 --> 33:57.202
That's your fault.

33:57.202 --> 33:58.912
You didn't give me any time
to lose a tail.

33:58.912 --> 34:01.373
What kind of sloppy protocols
is Armstrong teaching you?

34:01.373 --> 34:02.582
Why don't you ask him
yourself?

34:04.542 --> 34:06.002
[ Groans ]

34:06.002 --> 34:08.088
[ Laughs ]

34:08.088 --> 34:09.798
It was a nice play,
Nolan.

34:09.798 --> 34:11.383
It was a nice play.

34:11.383 --> 34:12.926
And it might've worked,
had I not called Ruben

34:12.926 --> 34:15.470
and told him you were
way too much of a Boy Scout

34:15.470 --> 34:16.763
to ever sell your soul.

34:17.764 --> 34:19.557
You wanna do
the honors?

34:22.269 --> 34:24.271
It'd actually be
my pleasure.

34:24.271 --> 34:26.815
Careful. Last time
you tried this, you missed.

34:26.815 --> 34:28.942
Yeah.
I made it too complicated.

34:28.942 --> 34:31.278
Having to pull the gun,
flip the chair.

34:31.278 --> 34:34.281
This is gonna be
much simpler.

34:34.281 --> 34:38.076
I'd ask for last words, but
I'm sick of hearing your voice.

34:38.076 --> 34:39.577
Wait!
[ Gun clicks ]

34:39.577 --> 34:40.912
What the...?

34:40.912 --> 34:49.379
♪♪

34:49.379 --> 34:57.637
♪♪

34:57.637 --> 35:06.229
♪♪

35:06.229 --> 35:14.529
♪♪

35:14.529 --> 35:22.996
♪♪

35:22.996 --> 35:24.539
[ Groans ]

35:24.539 --> 35:27.751
♪♪

35:27.751 --> 35:30.211
[ Gunshot echoes ]

35:30.211 --> 35:32.922
[ Footsteps approach ]

35:35.675 --> 35:38.094
[ Sighs ] Is he dead?

35:38.094 --> 35:40.597
Drop the gun!
Now. On the ground.

35:40.597 --> 35:41.765
Right now.

35:44.726 --> 35:46.478
Take out your phone.
Dial 911.

35:46.478 --> 35:49.397
Put it on speaker.
Place it next to your gun.

35:49.397 --> 35:52.025
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

35:52.025 --> 35:53.735
Woman: <i>911.</i>
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

35:53.735 --> 35:57.113
This is Officer John Nolan,
badge number 25253.

35:57.113 --> 35:58.907
I have multiple suspects
in custody.

35:58.907 --> 36:01.326
Requesting backup
and ambulances, plural.

36:01.326 --> 36:04.371
One victim,
multiple gunshot wounds.

36:04.371 --> 36:06.247
Status unknown.
Now, take off your clothes.

36:06.247 --> 36:07.207
<i>Excuse me?</i>

36:07.207 --> 36:08.708
Not you.

36:08.708 --> 36:10.543
Strip. Now.

36:10.543 --> 36:12.545
[ Breathing heavily ]

36:12.545 --> 36:17.967
♪♪

36:17.967 --> 36:23.348
♪♪

36:23.348 --> 36:25.558
Gunshot victim unconscious,
not breathing.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.609
[ Door opens ]

36:34.609 --> 36:36.403
So,
I'll make this quick.

36:36.403 --> 36:38.238
N.O.I.D.

36:38.238 --> 36:39.906
What does that stand for,
Officer Nolan?

36:39.906 --> 36:41.157
Notice of Intent
to Discipline.

36:41.157 --> 36:42.325
Why are you smiling?

36:42.325 --> 36:43.576
'Cause it means
I still have a job.

36:43.576 --> 36:44.661
Don't celebrate yet.

36:44.661 --> 36:46.246
You're not gonna like
what's coming.

36:46.246 --> 36:47.872
Neither will you,
Detective Harper.

36:47.872 --> 36:49.374
Sir, can I say something,
please?

36:49.374 --> 36:51.459
As a training officer,
I have one job,

36:51.459 --> 36:53.253
and that is
to teach Officer Nolan

36:53.253 --> 36:55.088
the right way
to be a cop.

36:55.088 --> 36:57.382
And...I failed.

36:57.382 --> 36:58.925
I should bear
all the consequences.

36:58.925 --> 37:00.135
Nyla, no.
Yes.

37:00.135 --> 37:03.179
As touching as this is,

37:03.179 --> 37:05.014
Officer Nolan has received
enough instruction

37:05.014 --> 37:06.307
to know
right from wrong.

37:06.307 --> 37:09.352
Clearly, I have given you both
way too much leeway.

37:09.352 --> 37:10.645
That's on me.

37:10.645 --> 37:13.523
What is Noble Cause Corruption,
Officer Nolan?

37:13.523 --> 37:15.900
When an officer justifies
bending or breaking the rules

37:15.900 --> 37:17.694
if they believe that infraction
is being done

37:17.694 --> 37:18.653
in the name of justice.

37:18.653 --> 37:20.113
The ends justify the means.

37:20.113 --> 37:23.116
The mind‐set
that bad behavior is okay

37:23.116 --> 37:24.743
as long as
it produces justice

37:24.743 --> 37:27.454
is a cancer.

37:27.454 --> 37:30.039
And it's long past time
we treat it as such.

37:30.039 --> 37:32.625
Big changes are being made
moving forward.

37:32.625 --> 37:34.753
Those changes are starting
right here, right now.

37:34.753 --> 37:36.004
You both will receive

37:36.004 --> 37:38.298
letters of reprimand
in your file.

37:38.298 --> 37:40.008
In addition,
Officer Nolan,

37:40.008 --> 37:41.551
you will be held over
the FTO program

37:41.551 --> 37:43.094
for an additional month,

37:43.094 --> 37:47.766
and you will have to pass
a Review Board Test to advance.

37:47.766 --> 37:49.517
Yes, sir.
To be clear,

37:49.517 --> 37:52.520
receiving a letter of reprimand
as a rookie

37:52.520 --> 37:53.772
is almost certain

37:53.772 --> 37:56.441
to keep you from advancing
in the department.

37:56.441 --> 37:59.152
So any hopes of joining
a specialized unit

37:59.152 --> 38:02.030
or making detective
should be abandoned.

38:02.030 --> 38:04.783
Given those constraints,
you will have to decide

38:04.783 --> 38:07.952
if the life of a patrol officer
is good enough for you.

38:10.538 --> 38:12.707
Alright, go home.
Get some rest.

38:14.584 --> 38:16.252
I am so sorry.
[ Scoffs ]

38:16.252 --> 38:17.629
John, I ‐‐
It's not your fault.

38:17.629 --> 38:18.963
It's kind of a lot
my fault.

38:18.963 --> 38:20.340
Nyla.

38:20.340 --> 38:23.259
What are you gonna do?

38:23.259 --> 38:24.677
Exactly what Grey said.

38:24.677 --> 38:26.262
I'm gonna go home,
I'm gonna go to bed,

38:26.262 --> 38:28.389
and in the morning,
I'm gonna get up and...

38:30.308 --> 38:31.810
...try to earn back
what I've lost.

38:31.810 --> 38:33.561
[ Black Gatsby's "The Price"
plays ]

38:33.561 --> 38:37.690
♪♪

38:37.690 --> 38:38.900
[ Door opens ]

38:38.900 --> 38:41.110
You were wrong earlier.

38:41.110 --> 38:44.197
About anything in particular,
or just in a global sense?

38:44.197 --> 38:46.157
You said
at the end of the day,

38:46.157 --> 38:48.451
we only think we know
other people, but you're wrong.

38:48.451 --> 38:50.411
Okay, Lucy ‐‐
No.

38:50.411 --> 38:52.455
When I was
in that barrel,

38:52.455 --> 38:53.832
I knew
you would find me.

38:54.833 --> 38:57.043
No matter what it took.

38:57.043 --> 39:00.129
I found you
because of your ring, okay?

39:00.129 --> 39:01.548
You saved yourself.

39:01.548 --> 39:02.882
And I really hope what happened
with Rosalind today

39:02.882 --> 39:04.175
doesn't screw
with your head.

39:06.094 --> 39:08.346
If it does,
I'll deal with it.

39:08.346 --> 39:10.557
And I know
you'll help me.

39:10.557 --> 39:12.475
Uh, it's not really part
of my job description.

39:12.475 --> 39:13.685
Mm‐hmm.

39:13.685 --> 39:16.312
Hey, uh,
I was wondering, um,

39:16.312 --> 39:19.274
well, Chris' funeral
is tomorrow, and...

39:19.274 --> 39:20.859
Look, is it okay
if I go home with you

39:20.859 --> 39:22.193
and we can just go together
in the morning?

39:22.193 --> 39:23.361
Of course.

39:23.361 --> 39:24.988
We could talk about
you joining I. A.

39:24.988 --> 39:26.614
on the way home.
Dad.

39:26.614 --> 39:30.201
Look, I'm not saying
you have to decide now,

39:30.201 --> 39:31.786
but if you really want to
make a difference

39:31.786 --> 39:33.204
in this department,

39:33.204 --> 39:34.581
you should think about it.

39:34.581 --> 39:35.915
I will.

39:35.915 --> 39:38.084
I promise.
Good.

39:38.084 --> 39:39.586
I'll ask you again
next week.

39:39.586 --> 39:42.714
I have no doubt.

39:42.714 --> 39:44.966
I'm taking a long bath
when we get home.

39:44.966 --> 39:46.301
I'm going
straight to bed.

39:46.301 --> 39:47.719
No, you're not.

39:47.719 --> 39:50.221
These dogs aren't gonna
rub themselves.

39:50.221 --> 39:52.223
Pregnant women
are very needy.

39:52.223 --> 39:53.975
I don't think
you're fully prepared.
Uh‐huh.

39:53.975 --> 39:56.394
Lopez,
I have some good news.

39:57.729 --> 39:59.355
Me, too.
Can I go first?

39:59.355 --> 40:00.732
It's the only
bright spot in my day.

40:00.732 --> 40:02.233
Sure.
What's up?

40:02.233 --> 40:04.903
It's been an honor
having you under my watch.

40:04.903 --> 40:06.946
What?
You will be reporting to

40:06.946 --> 40:09.073
Detective Sergeant Caradine
from now on.

40:09.073 --> 40:10.617
Your promotion
is official.

40:10.617 --> 40:12.160
Congratulations,
Detective.

40:12.160 --> 40:14.537
♪ This is the end ♪

40:14.537 --> 40:16.164
Thank you.

40:18.124 --> 40:19.959
Oh, I'm sorry.
So what's your good news?

40:19.959 --> 40:22.670
Uh, she's ‐‐
Um, going to take a bath

40:22.670 --> 40:24.422
and get my feet rubbed.

40:24.422 --> 40:27.008
Okay.

40:27.008 --> 40:28.927
Mine was definitely better,
but okay.

40:28.927 --> 40:30.595
Thank you, sir.

40:30.595 --> 40:31.930
It wouldn't have happened
without you.

40:31.930 --> 40:33.431
Have a great night,
you two.

40:33.431 --> 40:35.767
♪ Put the cash
right in my hand ♪

40:35.767 --> 40:37.977
Why didn't you want me
to tell him?

40:37.977 --> 40:39.771
I've been trying to
make detective for years.

40:39.771 --> 40:42.023
If I show up pregnant
on day one,

40:42.023 --> 40:43.608
that's all they'll ever
see me as.

40:43.608 --> 40:45.902
They'll treat me as fragile,
and I'll never get a real shot.

40:45.902 --> 40:47.904
Okay, so we keep it
a secret for now.

40:47.904 --> 40:49.489
For now.

40:49.489 --> 40:51.950
♪ On my way now,
on my way ♪

40:54.535 --> 40:56.788
[ Lock clicks, keys jingle ]

40:56.788 --> 40:58.539
[ Light switch clicks ]

40:58.539 --> 41:00.416
[ Sighs ]

41:05.964 --> 41:07.674
[ Cork pops ]

41:07.674 --> 41:09.592
[ Liquid pouring ]

41:09.592 --> 41:12.220
[ Bottle thuds ]

41:12.220 --> 41:14.222
[ Cellphone ringing ]

41:18.851 --> 41:21.229
[ Cellphone beeps, clicks ]
Hello?

41:21.229 --> 41:24.148
Congratulations.
I underestimated you.

41:24.148 --> 41:25.149
Rosalind.

41:25.149 --> 41:26.150
You won.

41:26.150 --> 41:28.069
I didn't win.

41:28.069 --> 41:30.279
People died.
People I care about.

41:30.279 --> 41:32.448
I know.
But there is a bright side.

41:32.448 --> 41:33.992
At least for me.

41:33.992 --> 41:38.287
Armstrong's criminality puts
all of his cases in jeopardy.

41:38.287 --> 41:39.539
<i>Including mine.</i>

41:39.539 --> 41:43.001
Rosalind, you are never
going to walk free.

41:43.001 --> 41:44.168
We both know that.

41:44.168 --> 41:47.130
Now, I'm hanging up,
I'm calling the prison,

41:47.130 --> 41:48.756
and they're gonna come
confiscate that phone you're on.

41:48.756 --> 41:50.800
I know.

41:50.800 --> 41:52.927
But it was worth it
to hear your voice.

41:52.927 --> 41:55.304
<i>I'll be dreaming abou‐‐</i>
[ Cellphone beeps, clicks ]

41:55.304 --> 41:57.515
[ Cellphone thuds ]

41:57.515 --> 41:59.308
[ Sighs ]

42:26.461 --> 42:34.635
♪♪

42:34.635 --> 42:43.102
♪♪

42:43.102 --> 42:51.360
♪♪
